The paper discusses the use of probabilistic amplitude shaping (PAS) in fiber-optic communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory and communication (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The use of coded modulation (CM) and forward error correction codes also suggests a focus on coding theory and data structures (cs.DS). The application of PAS to increase spectral efficiency may also involve network infrastructure and protocols (cs.NI) and signal processing and analysis (cs.SI).
